<h2>XRP vs Bitcoin in 2026: Which One Builds Generational Wealth?</h2>
<p>Bitcoin and XRP represent two very different visions of crypto’s future. Bitcoin is often called “digital gold” — a store of value with a fixed supply. XRP is designed as a fast, low-cost bridge for global payments. As of March 17, 2026, BTC trades around $74,300 while XRP sits near $1.50. Here’s a clear comparison to help you decide which (or both) fits your long-term wealth strategy.</p>

<h3>Quick Side-by-Side Comparison</h3>
